==English==
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Guantanamo [[bay|Bay]]'''

===Verb===
{Origin uncertain, but likely from the Spanish aguantar, to bear, endure, put up with + the colloquial no mo', no more} to be unable to bear; to find unacceptable, to refuse to [[endure]] for even one second longer. 

===Noun===
Origin uncertain, but in common use in Arabic-, Pashto-, and Urdu-speaking regions}  
#A the mythical final place of [[confinement]] of the great satan, immediately following the Great Upheaval but prior to the Grand Awakening and the Glorious Final Making Amends and Mellowing Out Forever After of that nation. 
#A a vast butterfly-and-wildflower preserve on the Caribbean island of Cuba. 

===Contraction===
Gitmo

